Steps to run the app:
• Install node.js from the website: https://nodejs.org/en/download/
• Using command prompt navigate to the project folder
• Install yarn using the command npm install --global yarn
• Install expo using the command npm i expo-cli
• Run the command yarn
• To start the application, open the virtual Android Device / or download Expo Go on an actual phone
then run the command: yarn start
then press a / or scan QR code with the phone

PS: all GitHub commits are done in one day because I've created the app in one day.
